<html metal:use-macro="context/@@marketing_template/master">
<body>
  <div id="about" metal:fill-slot="contents">
    <div id="primary">
      <h2>Bugs</h2>
      <h3 class="byline">Overview</h3>
    </div>

    <h2 class="headline">Cut the time it takes to translate your software</h2>

    <table id="features">
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <th>Translations for everyone</th>
          <th>Intelligent suggestions</th>
          <th>Works with GetText</th>
          <th>Uniquely flexible</th>
        </tr>
        <tr class="screenshots">
          <td><img src="/+icing/translations-feature-everyone.png"
                   alt="Translations for everyone mini screenshot" /></td>
          <td><img src="/+icing/translations-feature-suggestions.png"
                   alt="Translations suggestions mini screenshot" /></td>
          <td><img src="/+icing/translations-feature-gettext.png"
                   alt="Translations gettext mini screenshot" /></td>
          <td><img src="/+icing/translations-feature-flexible.png"
                   alt="Translations workflow mini screenshot" /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Launchpad simplifies software translation, making it easy for
              anyone to translate into their language.
          </td>
          <td>Automatic suggestions from 750,000 translated strings.</td>
          <td>Import .pot template files and export .po and .mo files of
            your translations.
          </td>
          <td>Maintain independent translation efforts for different
            releases and choose open, moderated or closed translation.
          </td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <div id="content">
      <div class="intro">
        <h3>About Launchpad Translations</h3>

        <p>Translators shouldn't have to be coders. Launchpad shields
           translators from low-level complexities, whilst working with
           standard .pot, .po and .mo files.
        </p>

        <p>Automatic suggestions, from a library of 750,000 translated
           strings, and a community of 19,000 registered translators can
           radically cut the time required to localise your project into many
           languages.
        </p>

        <p>Launchpad keeps track of the translations for each major version of
           a project separately, allowing translators to continue to improve
           the translations of your stable releases while others start work on
           newer versions that are still in development.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div> <!-- content -->
  </div>
</body>
</html>
